The '''Elqui-Limarí Batholith''' is a group of [[pluton]]s in the Andes of Chile and Argentina between the latitudes of 28 and 30° S. The plutons of the batholith were [[Methods of pluton emplacement|emplaced]] and cooled in the [[Paleozoic|Late Paleozoic]] and the [[Triassic|earliest Mesozoic]].<ref name=Panketal1996>{{cite journal|last=Pankhurst |first=Robert J. |last2=Millar |first2=Ian L. |last3=Hervé |first3=Francisco |author-link1=Robert John Pankhurst |author-link3=Francisco Hervé |date=1996 |title=A Permo-Carboniferous U-Pb age for part of the Guanta Unit of the Elqui-Limarí Batholith at Río del Tránsito, Northern Chile |url=http://www.andeangeology.equipu.cl/index.php/revista1/article/viewFile/V23n1-a03/2415 |journal=[[Andean Geology|Revista Geológica de Chile]] |publisher= |volume=23 |issue=1 |pages= |doi= |access-date=5 January 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126003033/http://www.andeangeology.equipu.cl/index.php/revista1/article/viewFile/V23n1-a03/2415 |archivedate=26 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> Some of the plutons were emplaced in a context of [[crustal thickening]] related to the [[San Rafael orogeny]].<ref name=KleimanJapas2009>{{cite journal |last=Kleiman |first=Laura E. |last2=Japas |first2=María S. |date=2009 |title=The Choiyoi volcanic province at 34°S–36°S (San Rafael, Mendoza, Argentina): Implications for the Late Palaeozoic evolution of the southwestern margin of Gondwana |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Laura_Kleiman/publication/241406241_The_Choiyoi_volcanic_province_at_34S-36S_%28San_Rafael_Mendoza_Argentina%29_Implications_for_the_Late_Palaeozoic_evolution_of_the_southwestern_margin_of_Gondwana/links/546b47370cf2f5eb18091754.pdf |journal=[[Tectonophysics (journal)|Tectonophysics]] |publisher= |volume=473 |issue= |pages=283–299 |doi= |access-date=5 January 2016}}</ref>
Together with the [[Coastal Batholith of central Chile|Chilean Coastal Batholith]] and the [[Colangüil Batholith]] the Elqui-Limarí Batholith is a remnant of the [[volcanic arc]]s that erupted the volcanic material of the [[Choiyoi Group]].<ref name=KleimanJapas2009/>
