{{Infobox astronaut | name = Liu Boming | image = Liu Boming.JPG | image_size = 160px | caption = Liu Boming speaking at the [[Chinese University of Hong Kong]] | type = [[China National Space Administration|CNSA]] Astronaut | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1966|9}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = | current_occupation = | previous_occupation = [[Fighter pilot]], [[People's Liberation Army Ground Force|PLAAF]] | rank = [[Major general]], [[People's Liberation Army Strategic Support Force|PLASSF]] | space_time = 2d 20h 18m | selection = [[List of astronauts by selection#1998|Chinese Group 1]] | missions = [[Shenzhou 7]] | insignia = [[File:Shenzhou 7 mission patch.png|40px]] | retirement = }} {{Chinese name|[[Liu]]}}
'''Liu Boming''' ({{zh|s=刘伯明|t=劉伯明|p=Líu Bómíng}}; born September 1966) is a Chinese [[aviator|pilot]] selected as part of the [[Shenzhou spacecraft|Shenzhou program]]. A [[fighter aircraft|fighter]] pilot in the [[People's Liberation Army Air Force]], he was selected to be an [[China National Space Administration|CNSA]] member in 1998.
==CNSA career== Liu, along with [[Zhai Zhigang]] and [[Jing Haipeng]], was chosen to be the main crew of ''[[Shenzhou 7]]'', with Zhai as commander, on 17 September 2008. On 25 September, at 21:10 CST, they launched into space as China's third [[human spaceflight]] mission, and the first Chinese mission ever to have a three-man crew. <ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2008-09/26/content_7060750.htm |title=Shenzhou VII launched for 1st spacewalk |last=Hu |first=Yinan |date=2008-09-26 |work=China Daily |access-date=2018-08-09 |last2=Xin |first2=Dingding |location=Jiuquan; Beijing}}</ref> Liu and Zhai participated in China's first-ever [[Extra-vehicular activity|space walk]].
Liu wore a Russian [[Orlan space suit|Orlan-M]] spacesuit, while Zhai wore the Chinese-made [[Feitian space suit]]. Liu remained in the open portal of the orbital module, assisting Zhai on his spacewalk; later in the space walk, Liu also performed a stand-up extra-vehicular activity, partially leaving the orbital module in order to hand Zhai a Chinese flag.<ref name="JSR601Draft">{{cite web |last=McDowell |first=Jonathan |url=http://planet4589.org/space/jsr/latest.html |title=JSR No. 601 draft |work=[[Jonathan's Space Report]] | date=2008-09-29 |accessdate=2008-09-29 }}</ref>
After the spacewalk, Liu said in an interview that his inspiration and idols have always been [[Neil Armstrong]] and [[Yuri Gagarin]]. <ref>{{Cite news |url=http://scitech.people.com.cn/GB/8099236.html |title=刘伯明：阿姆斯特朗是我的偶像 |last=Wu |first=Bing |date=2008-09-24 |work=People.net |access-date=2018-08-09 |last2=Sun |first2=Dejun |trans-title=Liu Boming: Neil Armstrong is my idol |last3=Wang |first3=Bing |last4=Liu |first4=Lifang |last5=Zhe |first5=Danzhu |last6=Jia |first6=Xubo}}</ref>
